name: Multi
description:
IF YOU ENJOY THE MODEL PLEASE RATE/REVIEW IT!!

I found that most models are to opinionated, hence the multi model. It excels at detailed prompts and doesn't try to turn everything into a human (but you still can generate the human's ofcourse).

For reference please check the images posted, for the first few I kept all the settings the same so to get the result all you have to do is copy the pos & neg prompt and you're done. The ones after that i just copied from other posts and posted the ones that came out. Thanks for those prompts.

I seem to run on coffee so if you want to keep me running, here is my coffee link (also taking custom requests in exchange for for a couple of double espressos, slide into dm): https://www.buymeacoffee.com/olliesd

recommended settings are:
DPM++ SDE
CLIP skip 1
for detailed prompts use high CFG.
Hires fix makes everything better!
no vea required

FYI if you're getting image collections instead of 1 images try tuning down the weights.


When prompting for people it'll tend to look like chilloutmix with some softer lighting. Although the same thing can easily be achieved by adding some shadow & skin related tags to your prompt.

This model is also surprisingly good at inpainting!

GLHF & IF YOU GENERATE ANY AWESOME IMAGES, SHARE THEM PLEASE :)
